A few weeks ago, an episode of The Late Show with Stephen Colbert opened with a sketch about a young woman who decides to go to the cinema. She calls a movie booking service called Moviefone (real, but now defunct) and selects a film in response to the automated prompt. This is how the scene plays out. The automated voice responds: “You have selected a movie that features an actor accused of sexual harassment.
 
